photo.title: By the Dawn's Early Light - New Year 2014

description._content:
A close friend of mine suggested staying overnight at the San Francisco Hyatt Embarcadero for the 2013 New Year's Eve fireworks.  Although we'd already watched the 2012 New Year's Eve  fireworks (but didn't stay overnight), I grabbed the chance in order to capture the Ferry Building in all its glory from the hotel which is just right across the street.  I've had seen a few shots of the Ferry Building here on Flickr from other photographers and I felt this is one heck of an opportunity to do it.    So I took a few shots of the building from our hotel balcony (before the fireworks), and then I thought maybe I should take a shot of it in early dawn of the new year to symbolize a new beginning or something :)      

Although we watched the fireworks from the streets (I suck at shooting fireworks anyway, so I opted not to shoot during the fireworks show, haha) and stayed up until 1 am, I dutifully woke myself up at 6:30 am which was just perfect timing as it is sunrise time during the winter season - as you can see from the shot above the clock face shows 6:45 am.  I captured quite a few shots and selected this shot  as my first work for 2014 to post on Flickr.  Hope you guys like it.

Thank you for your kind visits, friends,  and Happy New Year to you all!  Wishing you the best in your endeavors (photography and otherwise) and happiness and health to all of us!

photo.title: Under the Bay Bridge

description._content:
Here's wishing everyone a Happy New Year! 

This is the classic view of SF Skyline as seen from under the Bay Bridge. Came here 3 times in as many weeks! On the first try, it was too windy and thick clouds rolled in and created a grey layer right on top of the skyline. On the second try, the beacon did not light up at all! On both occasions, we thought the beacon will be on at 5 and that's why we made the trip despite the wind, etc which we knew were not favorable! Our intel was obviously wrong! HAHA! I finally got something I am happy with on my third attempt.

photo.title: Holiday Spirit 6

description._content:
Twin Peak, San Francisco, CA

We had some friends visiting us, so we cannot go out of town like previous years. We really enjoyed the celebration of holidays in SF. Watching SF ballet Nutcracker, Skating in a ice rink next to Ferry Building, Hanging around under the giant Christmas tree in Union Square, Dining in the premier restaurants, Staying in Hyatt Regency even though we only have 45 minutes driving to home. 

Believe or not, I have been in the Bay Area over 20 years, but I have not been in Twin Peak, the highest spot in San Francisco. Even though I have seen many images from this spot, all of us were jaw dropping on the scene when we climbed up to the hill. Fortunately, the TA building's Beacon was turned on at 5PM, so I can include the mini-star and LED-lited bay bridge in the same frame during the blue hour.

Happy Holidays!

description._content: Ex-New Orleans car 952 on the F Line, at the Embarcadero, by the Ferry Building, in summer 2009. The car was originally leased to MUNI in 1998 - and re-gauged from the 'Pennsylvania Trolley Gauge' of five feet two-and-a-half inches, The lease has subsequently been extended, and in 2005 another car - 913 - was purchased from the Orange Empire Railway Museum, for eventual restoration. Car 952 has been out of service in recent years, but is due to return to the F Line in 2014, after overhaul and refurbishment.. photo.title: Evening glow

description._content:
San Francisco in the evening. At left the west span of the bay bridge leading into San Francisco, with the Embarcadero and the famous ferry building on the right. All the way on the right, a part of Angel Island can be seen. Due to the 15 second exposure the 'dancing lights' of the Bay Bridge seem like simple lines along the suspension cables.

The image was taken from Pier 14 on a COLD (and clear) night.

I combined 9 portrait-orientation images into one file to create an 82 megapixel panorama at 3:1 aspect ratio. At 100% zoom incredible detail can be seen, such as people sitting on the benches on the main boulevard.
